reviews.text: Great place for spotting ostentatious vulgarity.

The station and the high street close by had a very village look. Cosy little platforms were a pleasure to watch and use. Now they have built those giant ugly stair blocks with poor optics and appeal. It is a great effort to spoil the character from a great British affluent village station to middle class urban unattractive structure.
Great station with lots of improvements - only missing British smile at the tickets office.
There are fast and slow trains to london from here. Double check that the first train to London is the fastest. There is plenty of council run parking behind the station. It is never full.
The station has been improved thanks to the new DDA footbridge with lifts and relocated but could still do with more shade and seating.
